        public boolean add(E element)
        Adds an element to the end of the recursive list. If the list is empty, the add is handled entirely within this method. If not, it is passed down and handled recursively by the inner ListNode class
        Parameters:
        element - element to add to the list
        Returns:
        true if the element can be added

      • add

        public void add(int index,
                E element)
        Adds an element to the list at a particular index. If the index is negative or is greater that the number of elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown. If the element is null, then a NullPointerException is thrown. If the index is not 0, then the process is handled by the recursive inner method.
        Parameters:
        index - index to add the element to
        element - element to add to the list

      • get

        public E get(int index)
        Finds the element at a particular index. If the searched index is less than 0 or greater than the number of elements in the list, an IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown. If the index =/= 0, then the process is handled by the recursive inner function.
        Parameters:
        index - index of element we are looking for
        Returns:
        element at a particular index

      • remove

        public boolean remove(E element)
        Removes an element from the list. if the element is not the first element in the list, the process is handled by the inner recursive method.
        Parameters:
        element - element we are looking to remove
        Returns:
        true if the element can be removed, false if not (meaning that the element didn't exist in the list to begin with)

      • remove

        public E remove(int index)
        Removes the element at a particular index. If the index is less than 0 or greater than the number of elements in the list, an IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown. If the index =/= 0, the process is passed down to the inner recursive function.
        Parameters:
        index - index of element we are looking to remove
        Returns:
        element that is removed.

      • set

        public E set(int index,
             E element)
        Replaces the element at a particular index with a different index. If the index is less than 0 or greater than the number of elements in the list, an IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown. If the element is null, a NullPointerException is thrown. If the index =/= 0, the process is passed down and handled by the inner recursive method.
        Parameters:
        index - index of element to be replaced
        element - element to be assigned to the index
        Returns:
        element that was replaced
